*----->✅ 1. Functional Requirements<-----*
(What the program should do)
1.Display traffic rules
2.Accept user input (menu choice)
3.Check speed and calculate fine
4.Check helmet usage
5.Check seatbelt usage
6.Display appropriate messages (fine / no fine)
7.Exit option for user

*----->✅ 2. Non-Functional Requirements<-----*
(How the program should behave)
1.Simple and user-friendly interface
2.Fast execution
3.Accurate results
4.Easy to understand code (modular functions)

*----->✅ 3. Hardware Requirements<-----*
1.Computer / Laptop
2.Minimum 2GB RAM
3.Keyboard (for input)
          
*----->✅ 4. Software Requirements<-----*
1.C Compiler (like Turbo C, GCC, or Code::Blocks)
2.Operating System (Windows / Linux / Mac)
          
*----->✅ 5. Input Requirements<-----*
1.User choice (1–5)
2.Speed value
3.Helmet input (1 or 0)
4.Seatbelt input (1 or 0)
          
*----->✅ 6. Output Requirements<-----*
1.Traffic rules display
2.Fine messages (₹500 / ₹1000)
3.Safe driving messages
4.Exit message
